OL,3,CHousing association tops London list
OL,4,Cof prevention of future death orders
OL,6,FITV London reporter, Kaf Okpattah, has
OL,7,Fbeen speaking to the families of
OL,8,Fvictims.
OL,10,FOne of London's oldest, and largest,
OL,11,Fhousing associations has been given
OL,12,Fmore prevention of future death orders
OL,13,Fthan any other in the capital, an
OL,14,Finvestigation by ITV London has found.
OL,16,FPeabody Housing was founded in 1862
OL,17,Fand according to their website,
OL,18,Fcurrently oversees 108,000 homes and
OL,19,F220,000 residents.
