OL,6,FPeabody hadn't kept records of Tina's
OL,7,Finstructions to them, nor had they
OL,8,Fpassed it on to Elizabeth's support
OL,9,Fworkers.
OL,11,FFollowing Elizabeth's death, the
OL,12,Fcoroner did not say whether contacting
OL,13,FTina would have save Mrs. Pamment's
OL,14,Flife but did clarify it would have
OL,15,Fsignificantly improved her physical
OL,16,Fand emotional comfort.
OL,18,F"The night that she fell as the first
OL,19,Ftime she called for assistance and we
OL,20,Fnow know they did not call me," added
OL,21,FTina.
